				<h2 class="posttitle"><a href="http://www.lightningrodlabs.com/?p=320" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Making use of mistakes">Making use of mistakes</a></h2>
				<div class="postmetadata">6th May 2010, 08:21 am  <!-- by rod --></div>
				<div class="postentry">
					<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-319" title="Donna's_west_Garden_2010" src="http://www.lightningrodlabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/Donnas_west_Garden_2010.JPG" alt="Donna's_west_Garden_2010" width="1000" height="651" /> Some time back I showed pictures of a railing I made for my son&#8217;s garage. In my usual fashion, I sped ahead without checking the building code for the spacing of uprights.   We were unable to use it because of this . I set the thing aside in my shop, wondering what to do with it. My wife, Donna spotted it while she was doing her gardens. Being clever and artistic she came up with a neat use for it.</p>
<p>The picture above shows her west garden which is one of many. This one is secluded behind the house and was carved from the brush.  I think they look interesting and attractive there. Hopefully they will cause the deer to detour around the garden.  As the spring progresses and the flowers grow, the garden will look even more beautiful.</p>
				</div>
		
